s:2100:"<p><strong style="font-size:0.9375rem;">Course Completion Description: Physics Fundamentals</strong><br /></p><p><strong><br /></strong></p><p>To complete the <strong>Physics Fundamentals</strong> course and achieve a minimum grade of 50%, demonstrate proficiency in the following areas:</p><p><strong><br /></strong></p><p></p><ol><li><strong>Attendance and Engagement: </strong>Attend all lectures, participate actively in discussions, and engage in practical demonstrations and experiments.</li><li><strong style="font-size:0.9375rem;">Assignments and Assessments: </strong><span style="font-size:0.9375rem;">Complete assigned readings, homework, and laboratory reports on time. Successfully pass quizzes, tests, and examinations based on course content.</span></li><li><strong style="font-size:0.9375rem;">Conceptual Understanding: </strong><span style="font-size:0.9375rem;">Master foundational principles such as mechanics (kinematics, dynamics, statics), thermodynamics, electricity and magnetism, and waves and optics.</span></li><li><strong style="font-size:0.9375rem;">Application Skills: </strong><span style="font-size:0.9375rem;">Apply physics concepts to solve problems, calculate forces, analyze energy transformations, and interpret wave behaviours.</span></li><li><strong style="font-size:0.9375rem;">Critical Thinking and Analysis</strong><strong style="font-size:0.9375rem;">: </strong><span style="font-size:0.9375rem;">Demonstrate critical thinking skills by analyzing experimental data, interpreting diagrams, and making evidence-based conclusions.</span></li><li><strong style="font-size:0.9375rem;">Presentation of Learning: </strong><span style="font-size:0.9375rem;">Present findings and analyses effectively, demonstrating an understanding of complex physics concepts and their practical applications.</span></li></ol><p><strong><br /></strong></p><p><span>By meeting these criteria, you showcase your ability to comprehend and apply fundamental physics principles. This accomplishment prepares you for further studies and applications in physics-related fields.</span></p>";